WHS will return to school with a hybrid schedule beginning Monday, Sept 14, until at least the end of the 1st quarter. WGS will continue as normal for now with noon dismissals on Fridays for remote learning.

WHS Hybrid Schedule
Group A: Last names A-L, in-person Mon, Wed; remote Tues, Thurs, Fri
Group B: M-Z, in-person Tues, Thurs; remote Mon, Wed, Fri
*WHS will dismiss at 2:10 each day, Mon-Fri.

WGS will continue 100% in-person learning with 2:10 dismissals Mon-Thurs and a noon dismissal on Fridays.

For more detailed information, check your email or the school webpage, or email ehelbig@woodlawnschools.org. You may also refer to a FAQ page regarding the district’s plans by following the following link. https://docs.google.com/document/d/1FIgiKNYbcY-qm5_zlFnteYO3_Zr__gOlQQ9OyMyiXyo/edit?usp=sharing

post_text:
The following a synopsis of baseball/softball event guidance as sent out by the SIJHSAA. The following rules will be in effect for WHS fall baseball games as well.

Fans
- All fans must wear a mask, unless 6ft social distancing can be maintained or are actively eating or drinking.
- Fans may sit in groups of up to 50, but they must wear a mask if social distancing cannot be maintained.
o Multiple groups of 50 are allowed if at least 30 feet separate the groups.
Coaches and Players
- Athletes must be at least 6 feet apart in dugout areas, or players seated 6 feet apart behind the dugout.
- Players and coaches must wear a mask on the bus as well. Players should be spread out on the bus to the greatest extent possible.

Sara Hefner Hays
August 12 at 5:42 PM ·

The following is just a brief, condensed breakdown to make sure parents are aware of some changes that have been put in place. I know a lot of information has been sent your way and it may get confusing on what's what.
Hopefully this will help simplify a few things!

MONDAY, AUGUST 17- First day of school!
Doors will not open until 8:15. Students will not be allowed in the building until 8:15.

This day is a noon dismissal (12:00) day.
There will NOT be a lunch served on Monday.

TUESDAY, AUGUST 18- 2:10 dismissal begins

The 2:10 dismissal will continue until further notice.
Please also remember, students cannot be dropped off at the school prior to 8:15.
This is definitely going to be a starting year like no other before! Hopefully we will all be able to adjust accordingly, have patience and make this school year great!
I'm looking forward to seeing all the students again! (At least their eyes anyway! 😷😉)

post_text:
Moments ago, the Illinois State Board of Education released guidance for the 2020-'21 school year. We don't have much to share at this time as this 60 page document was released to schools at the same time it was shared with the public, so we will need time to read through the document and figure out exactly how it will affect our schools.

While we have anticipated some elements of the guidance, it will still take us some time to come up with a plan for resuming school. Please be patient with us, and we will release a plan as soon as possible.

WHS volleyball and girls basketball open gym annoucement:

Volleyball will be having open gyms starting July 1 from 8-10am (as long as the state moves into phase 4 and the IHSA's return to play guidelines are approved by the IDPH). Open gyms will continue on Mon and Wed in July at the same time.

WHS girls basketball open gyms will start Mon July 6 from 10am-12pm. Open gyms will be Mon, Wed, Thurs in the month of July.

All students intending to try out in these sports are encouraged to attend. Please arrive 10 min early so safety precautions can be completed before working out.

post_text:
The district will be updating the school calendar to show the last day of school as May 12 and May 6-12 will be designated as Remote Learning Planning Days. As a result, the last batch of school work for both WGS and WHS will have a due date of 5/5, which will be the last day of school for students who have completed work to earn a grade of "pass." If your child is having trouble completing assignments, please contact the school and we will make arrangements.

Parents of WGS students who have personal belongings to be picked up can pick up those items during lunch pick up on Monday. The last day for lunch service will be May 11, but the lunches will still cover that entire week.

We are still working on contingency plans for WHS and WGS graduation ceremonies and we will release information when a plan has been decided.

Additionally, the IHSA announced the cancellation of the 2020 spring sports tournaments yesterday.

post_text: As we wrap up this year remotely, I want to recognize an individual that should be getting more public recognition. Heath Ellis is the WGS recipient that should have attended the Principal's Collegiate Network Recognition Dinner in Jefferson County. He was chosen to receive this honor because of his academic achievement and moral character. Heath also didn't get the opportunity to compete at the Regional Bowling Match. I believe he would have qualified for State competition as well. If you get the chance, you might send him a message of congratulations. I'm proud of you, Heath, and wish you the best in life! I look forward to seeing what you achieve in life. Ms.Kabat

Woodlawn High School Title I Remote Learning

Woodlawn High School offers Title I Services to all students and these services are funded through federal grants. Ordinarily, students can take advantage of these services by attending tutoring sessions with Mrs. Hodge during study hall and/or after school on Tuesdays and Thursdays. Mrs. Hodge is still available during this remote learning process. If interested, you may email Mrs. Hodge at khodge@woodlawnschools.org with your questions or to request a live individual video session appointment.

Today, Governor Pritzker announced all schools will be closed in Illinois beginning on Tuesday, March 17 and may reopen on Tuesday, March 31. Additional learning activities may be sent home on Monday to enhance our students' education while the closure remains in effect.

Additionally, Woodlawn USD #209 will suspend all after school activities beginning Monday, March 16, and will resume activities at the end of the closure period.

As more information becomes available will be sure to share it as this situation develops.

The Edwards County IHSA girls basketball regional will be streamed on the NFHS network.

To watch games in the Albion 1-A Girls Regional, go to www.nfhsnetwork.com. At the top of the page that comes up, there is a blank line labeled “Type in your school, event, association, etc”. Type in the name of your school.
The school should pop up among suggestions. Click on your school.
If you are not already a subscriber to the NFHS webcasts, click on Subscribe in the upper right hand corner and follow the directions. The cost is $9.95 which will be good for any games you want to watch, past, present and future for 1 month. This would include any future girls or boys postseason games that might be streamed on the NFHS network.

Woodlawn will take on Christopher tonight at 6pm.

post_text: The grade school boy's basketball team plays their first game tomorrow morning at Rend Lake College in the State finals at 9:30am!!! If you aren't doing anything, come out and support WGS! Those attending need to be aware that SIJHSAA prohibits the use of all types of noise-makers, confetti, radios, shakers, poms(unless used by cheerleaders), rally towels, thunder sticks, camera lights, laser lights, and also tripods in the stands. Signs must be no larger than a legal sized sheet of paper. (8 1/2 X 14) Body painting materials shall not be administered at games or containers brought on game sites. Body paint may be worn on arms and the face. Therefore, put your face paint on before attending the game. See you there!
